<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Nimblefoot</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Wandered around Freeport, but didn't find anything new for smithing. Anyone found something?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Lothlin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Verant isn't going to make it easy for us, chances are, if you're looking for new Smithing items/receipes, some Jewellery- parts-selling-NPC will have it.  In the middle of Lavastorm.  I don't mean to discourge you on your Smithing efforts, but if EQ was easy, who would bother to return to it?<P>Besides, role-playing right?  don't be one- dimensional, keep trying various skills or receipes or spell-researching.  <P>Good Luck!  sorry that I couldn't actually answer your question!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Arthura</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Just letting you know...in the imports shop in Freeport you can find a new smithing book and several new molds. The molds combind to make 3 new weapons. A forged morning star, a forged two handed sword and a forged bastard sword. I've made a morning star and the damage is 8 with a delay of 38. At a skill of 126 it was trivial. <P>Arthura, Ranger of Karanas<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Talisman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">the new weapon molds are also in neriak</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Bard Valmi (Tunare)</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The book is in one of the shops in North Karana, near the Wood Brigde I think.  I traded some studs to a Tailor who'd picked it up coming from HPass.  Does have "recipies" for the new molds.  Holler if anyone learns needed levels to create.  I'm just at 33.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">jelenar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Supposedly, in the new patch banded gloves were added. If anyone knows where to find glove molds, let me know. It seems that the new shaman armor requires a piece of banded as a component and the high lvl shamans on my server cant get the gloves because no one knows where the banded gloves molds are.<P>Thanks</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Dimentox</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Its at 3 huts outside kaladim</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Yay!</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I forged a 2 handed sword, I used these components:<P>1 flask of water<BR>1 sheet of metal<BR>1 Heavy blade mold<BR>1 Hilt mold<BR>1 pommel mold<P>Result:<BR>Forged 2 handed sword<BR>12dmg 44dly<P>Costs about 5-6 plat to make<P>Trivial at my skill which is 140.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ruirik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">If dimentex meant that glove molds are at the three huts outside of Kaladim, he was wrong.  I went there and there are no glove molds.  The new weapon molds are there though.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">charixz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I have heard many rumors that on one of the islands in the Ocean of Tears is a place to buy the elusive Banded Guantlet Molds....truth or validity...remains to be seen by me....let me know if you find them there.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Sildan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The banded gauntlet molds are found in kelethin.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Brax</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The Banded Gauntlet Molds are at the Three Huts outside Ogguk.  Go to bridge over river and take a left before you cross it when leaving Ogguk.  First group of huts there and one of the Female Ogres has them.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Joxer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">ummm you can also find the glove molds in Everfrost Peaks.....near the enterance to Halas.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Nicophorus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Heh, the Banded Gauntlet Molds are also in that Mecca of Smithing known as Freeport, my wonderful hometown!<P>But, my real question is:<P>The new 10 slot forge as opposed to 6 slots?<P>What does it mean?<P>Nicophorus,<BR>Paladin of Mithaniel<BR>Brell Sirilus Server<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Chelovek</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">med sized gauntlet molds are in kelethin, large sized gauntlet molds are at the merchants in everfrost right before the halas zone.  i'm sure there are others, but these i've seen, purchased and produced,<BR>and they aren't trivial at a measely 119.<P>warrior of undetermined rank<BR>tallon zek<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
